article.description: Kindred Wesemann made eight 3-pointers for a career-high 25 points and Kansas State beat No. 20 Texas 66-57 on Wednesday.
article.shortLinkText: Wesemann-led KSU takes down No. 20 Texas
article.headline: Kansas State prolific from long range in win over No. 20 Texas
article.linkText: Wesemann-led KSU takes down No. 20 Texas
article.story:
MANHATTAN, Kan. -- Kindred Wesemann made eight 3-pointers for a career-high 25 points and Kansas State beat No. 20 Texas 66-57 on Wednesday.

Wesemann's last two 3-pointers came on consecutive possessions, sparking a 14-2 run that stretched a one-point lead to 61-48 with 1:07 left. The freshman finished 8 of 11 from long-range with four steals to help the Wildcats (14-7, 4-6 Big 12) win their third straight.

Ashia Woods added 13 points while Breanna Lewis and Shaelyn Martin added 10 apiece. The Wildcats took the lead for good at 35-34 on Woods' free throw with 12:44 left.

Ariel Atkins led Texas (15-6, 4-6) with 18 points. Kelsey Lang and Imani McGee-Stafford added 14 each.

McGee-Stafford had 10 points and four of her seven blocks in the first half as Texas held a 28-25 lead at the break. Wesemann had four 3-pointers in the first half to help Kansas State stay close.
